The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Friday, July 09, 2004  IN THE CITY
				 																																																	The IFA on Thursday slapped punishments on four Bengal players  Amjad Ali, Sainik Dey, Syed Rahim Nabi and Madhab Das  for assaulting referee A. Siddiqui during the under-21 junior national final in Jamalpur last month.				 																																																	IFA secretary Subrata Datta announced after the disciplinary committees meeting that Nabi, Madhab and Sainik have been suspended for two matches and fined Rs 15,000 each.				 																																																	Amjad, who has been suspended by the AIFF till the final disposal of the case, was also fined Rs 15,000 and ordered to pay up within 15 days.				 																																																	Both the coach and managers reports pulled up the erring players after Bengal lost the final 1-4.				 																																																	 Bhaichung Bhutia on Thursday practised with the East Bengal team for the first time this new season. Practising doesnt mean that Im signing for them (East Bengal) I havent made up my mind yet, Bhutia said after his workout. The India captain is likely to appear for trials at a Cyprus club later this month.				 																																																	 Two hattricks were recorded in the Calcutta League on Thursday. Dipanjan Saha of Suburban achieved it in the fourth division tie versus Beleghata Friends Union, as did Tara Friends Somnath Chakraborty against Shibsankar SC.				 																																																	FOOTBALL: Calcutta League Super Division: Mohun Bagan vs Wari (Mohun Bagan); Ever-Ready vs Peerless (Salt Lake Central Park). Matches from 3.30 pm. First Division group A: City vs Taltala DS (Tarun Sangha); SAIL vs Police AC (Howrah Stadium); ECL SA vs BNR (Barasat Stadium); Aryan vs WB Police (Rabindra Sarobar Stadium); Muslim Institute vs Howrah Union (Md. Sporting); Milan Bithee vs Kalighat (Juger Pratik). Matches from 3.30 pm.				 																																																	GOLF: The Telegraph Merchants Cup: Final days tee-off at 8 am, RCGC.
